00:56:26.410 --> 00:56:31.990 align:middle line:90%


00:56:31.990 --> 00:56:33.580 align:middle line:90%
It is a straight line.

00:56:33.580 --> 00:56:40.670 align:middle line:90%


00:56:40.670 --> 00:56:42.180 align:middle line:90%
The well-spaced example.

00:56:42.180 --> 00:56:51.390 align:middle line:90%


00:56:51.390 --> 00:56:59.710 align:middle line:84%
So well-spaced example
looks like this.

00:56:59.710 --> 00:57:06.110 align:middle line:84%
It's a straight line of
slope 2 up to the height T,

00:57:06.110 --> 00:57:09.370 align:middle line:90%
and then it's a horizontal line.

00:57:09.370 --> 00:57:10.810 align:middle line:90%
It's a flat line after that.

00:57:10.810 --> 00:57:14.950 align:middle line:90%


00:57:14.950 --> 00:57:17.310 align:middle line:90%
Cool.

00:57:17.310 --> 00:57:17.810 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:57:17.810 --> 00:57:22.430 align:middle line:84%
And now I can tell you what
is the semi well-spaced set.

00:57:22.430 --> 00:57:24.170 align:middle line:90%
So here's what we do.

00:57:24.170 --> 00:57:26.990 align:middle line:90%


00:57:26.990 --> 00:57:30.870 align:middle line:84%
So semi well-space
definition is now.

00:57:30.870 --> 00:57:35.050 align:middle line:84%
So T is going to be in between
minus S and S. That's good.

00:57:35.050 --> 00:57:39.070 align:middle line:84%
That's the region we
don't already understand.

00:57:39.070 --> 00:57:42.910 align:middle line:84%
So E delta is going to
be delta to the minus T.

00:57:42.910 --> 00:57:46.750 align:middle line:84%
So that point there is going to
be in our branching function.

00:57:46.750 --> 00:57:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And then what I will do is I
draw here a line with slope S,

00:57:53.270 --> 00:57:58.870 align:middle line:84%
and here a line with slope
2 minus S. By the way,

00:57:58.870 --> 00:58:00.330 align:middle line:90%
S is between 0 and 1.

00:58:00.330 --> 00:58:02.550 align:middle line:90%
So 2 minus S is the bigger one.

00:58:02.550 --> 00:58:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And I extend these
lines until they meet.

00:58:05.400 --> 00:58:06.400 align:middle line:90%
They'll meet somewhere.

00:58:06.400 --> 00:58:09.840 align:middle line:90%


00:58:09.840 --> 00:58:15.580 align:middle line:84%
And then the branching
function F of X

00:58:15.580 --> 00:58:21.260 align:middle line:84%
has to lie above this stuff,
and it has to go there.

00:58:21.260 --> 00:58:23.010 align:middle line:84%
That's the definition
of semi well spaced.

00:58:23.010 --> 00:58:27.380 align:middle line:90%


00:58:27.380 --> 00:58:28.620 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:58:28.620 --> 00:58:31.380 align:middle line:84%
So Reyn and Wang,
they proved that

00:58:31.380 --> 00:58:36.700 align:middle line:84%
in the semi well-spaced
case, this theorem is true.

00:58:36.700 --> 00:58:38.620 align:middle line:90%
And we won't do the whole proof.

00:58:38.620 --> 00:58:42.220 align:middle line:84%
But the proof is a variant
on what we saw here,

00:58:42.220 --> 00:58:44.380 align:middle line:84%
where you combine
in a clever way

00:58:44.380 --> 00:58:48.420 align:middle line:84%
the Fourier method and the
double counting method.

00:58:48.420 --> 00:58:52.180 align:middle line:84%
And at a very high
level, this setup is--

00:58:52.180 --> 00:58:54.300 align:middle line:84%
this slope 2 minus
S is the slope

00:58:54.300 --> 00:58:56.740 align:middle line:90%
where the Fourier method works.

00:58:56.740 --> 00:58:59.220 align:middle line:84%
And this slope S is the slope
where the double counting

00:58:59.220 --> 00:59:01.050 align:middle line:90%
method works.

00:59:01.050 --> 00:59:04.290 align:middle line:84%
And so this picture turns out to
be the situation where you can

00:59:04.290 --> 00:59:08.840 align:middle line:90%
combine those two methods well.

00:59:08.840 --> 00:59:09.340 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:59:09.340 --> 00:59:11.850 align:middle line:90%


00:59:11.850 --> 00:59:13.090 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:59:13.090 --> 00:59:15.570 align:middle line:84%
So now let's think about
what happens when we

00:59:15.570 --> 00:59:17.430 align:middle line:90%
do this multi-scale argument.

00:59:17.430 --> 00:59:19.670 align:middle line:84%
What happens to the
branching functions?

00:59:19.670 --> 00:59:22.380 align:middle line:84%
In other words, I
start with this setup,

00:59:22.380 --> 00:59:23.630 align:middle line:90%
I want to understand this guy.

00:59:23.630 --> 00:59:26.450 align:middle line:84%
And it depends on the
branching function of E delta.

00:59:26.450 --> 00:59:29.610 align:middle line:84%
