balls in a segment like that.

01:02:01.230 --> 01:02:03.330 align:middle line:90%
Now, why is it counting that?

01:02:03.330 --> 01:02:05.550 align:middle line:90%
Who is EB?

01:02:05.550 --> 01:02:11.810 align:middle line:84%
EB are the delta balls in the
rho ball in B. And TB are--

01:02:11.810 --> 01:02:16.510 align:middle line:84%
I take the tubes and
I just take the part

01:02:16.510 --> 01:02:22.230 align:middle line:90%
of the tube that is in the--

01:02:22.230 --> 01:02:25.388 align:middle line:90%
that's in the ball.

01:02:25.388 --> 01:02:25.930 align:middle line:90%
AUDIENCE: OK.

01:02:25.930 --> 01:02:36.290 align:middle line:84%
So then R E rho, that's the
number of rho balls in the rho 2

01:02:36.290 --> 01:02:41.550 align:middle line:84%
based on the product is just
the number that amounts to 2.

01:02:41.550 --> 01:02:43.470 align:middle line:90%
LAWRENCE GUTH: Right.

01:02:43.470 --> 01:02:45.670 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:02:45.670 --> 01:02:46.370 align:middle line:90%
Right.

01:02:46.370 --> 01:02:50.470 align:middle line:84%
So at T rho is this
blue tube and R of E rho

01:02:50.470 --> 01:02:54.500 align:middle line:84%
T rho is the number of rho
balls in the blue tube.

01:02:54.500 --> 01:02:56.200 align:middle line:84%
And then if we take
an orange tube,

01:02:56.200 --> 01:03:00.060 align:middle line:84%
it will go through this
